# Windows File System & Permissions

Windows primarily uses the NTFS file system.

## NTFS Features
- File and folder permissions
- Encryption (EFS)
- Compression
- Disk quotas
- Large file support

## NTFS Permissions
- Full Control: Complete access
- Modify: Read, write, delete
- Read & Execute: View and run files
- Read: View file contents
- Write: Create and modify files

## Key Rules
- Deny permissions override Allow
- Permissions can be inherited from parent folders
- Effective permissions determine actual access

